WEBVTT

00:01.358 --> 00:02.817
<i>Previously on Nashville...</i>

00:02.818 --> 00:03.998
I love you.

00:03.999 --> 00:05.433
It didn't mean anything.

00:05.434 --> 00:08.289
I'm so happy that you
agreed to open for Juliette.

00:08.290 --> 00:10.718
Win back those fans
and those radio stations

00:10.719 --> 00:12.033
one city at a time.

00:12.034 --> 00:13.282
Luke: I knew as soon as I heard it

00:13.283 --> 00:14.933
it was gonna be a hit single. Cheers.

00:14.934 --> 00:16.585
Have you ever worked as
a backup singer before?

00:16.586 --> 00:18.671
This is a recording of my church solo.

00:18.981 --> 00:21.094
- Maddie Claybourne.
- What?

00:21.095 --> 00:23.544
Now I understand why Deacon always
seems to be in the middle of it.

00:23.545 --> 00:25.468
It was a terrible, awful mistake.

00:25.469 --> 00:26.661
What was a mistake?

00:26.662 --> 00:27.882
We're done. Do you get that?

00:27.883 --> 00:28.853
Where are you going?

00:28.854 --> 00:30.334
You don't get to know that anymore, okay?!

00:35.907 --> 00:37.003
[Sighs]

00:39.000 --> 00:45.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:59.141 --> 01:00.309
Hey.

01:00.310 --> 01:01.601
Hey.

01:02.357 --> 01:03.944
[Sighs] How you doin'?

01:04.778 --> 01:07.611
Listen, I-I know what I said
about needing time and all that,

01:07.612 --> 01:09.896
but I shouldn't have reacted
the way I did, and I'm sorry.

01:09.897 --> 01:11.900
Man, it got crazy last night.

01:11.901 --> 01:13.042
[Chuckling] Yeah.

01:13.447 --> 01:14.587
The thing is...

01:14.973 --> 01:18.149
[Sighs] I got a sore spot
when it comes to Deacon.

01:18.666 --> 01:19.863
You do?

01:19.864 --> 01:21.130
Yeah, it goes way back.

01:21.131 --> 01:23.595
You remember the '92 Oklahoma state fair?

01:23.596 --> 01:25.563
- Yeah, you know I do.
- Yeah.

01:26.044 --> 01:28.326
Two of us stuck up on the
top of that Ferris wheel...

01:28.327 --> 01:30.495
best seats in the house
for the George Strait show.

01:30.496 --> 01:31.826
Yeah, but before that.

01:31.827 --> 01:33.513
Before we hit the midway,

01:33.514 --> 01:35.937
you know, we were still
a bunch of nobodies,

01:35.938 --> 01:38.044
had to play that tent
outside the livestock,

01:38.045 --> 01:39.520
and you were about to start your set,

01:39.521 --> 01:42.487
but couldn't find Deacon anywhere.

01:42.488 --> 01:44.040
And you sat in for him.

01:44.041 --> 01:45.395
- Yeah.
- I remember.

01:45.724 --> 01:48.251
Never could understand how you
put up with it all those years...

01:48.252 --> 01:50.861
the way he treated you,
the way he disappeared.

01:50.862 --> 01:52.080
Anyway...

01:53.052 --> 01:55.531
You were still pretty torn
up about it after your set,

01:55.532 --> 01:59.407
so I thought, you know, "maybe this is it.

01:59.408 --> 02:00.663
"Maybe...

02:01.632 --> 02:05.667
This is the night she finally... Sees me."

02:07.394 --> 02:10.780
But even alone together on top
of the world in that Ferris wheel

02:10.781 --> 02:13.239
with George Strait
singing "Cross my Heart,"

02:13.923 --> 02:16.101
all you could talk about was Deacon.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.399
That's how it was back then.

02:18.400 --> 02:21.484
But we're here now, right?

02:21.485 --> 02:22.597
Mm-hmm.

02:22.598 --> 02:24.622
- And I'm damn happy about it.
- Me too.

02:24.623 --> 02:26.161
[Cellphone rings, vibrates]

02:26.162 --> 02:28.450
- Oh, this is Bucky. I should probably...
- No.

02:28.451 --> 02:29.551
Hey.

02:30.633 --> 02:31.594
That's impossible.

02:31.595 --> 02:34.225
It told her to take it
down, and she said she did.

02:34.745 --> 02:36.577
<i>Well, it's really none of our business</i>

02:36.578 --> 02:38.262
<i>who this girl's father is, is it?</i>

02:38.263 --> 02:39.634
<i>Shepherd: Oh, wake up, Barbara.</i>

02:39.635 --> 02:41.221
<i>You say that, but you got
to know how people are.</i>

02:41.222 --> 02:42.878
<i>Everybody loves a dirty, little secret,</i>

02:42.879 --> 02:44.583
<i>and this girl is a love child.</i>

02:44.584 --> 02:46.224
<i>Oh, God, really? A love child?</i>

02:46.225 --> 02:48.091
<i>Jenny, listen, her mom is Rayna Jaymes,</i>

02:48.092 --> 02:50.767
<i>and then her father is
supposedly the mayor of Nashville,</i>

02:50.768 --> 02:52.353
<i>but then she posted a video</i>

02:52.354 --> 02:55.323
<i>using her mom's old boyfriend's last name.</i>

02:55.324 --> 02:56.234
<i>Hello?</i>

02:56.235 --> 02:58.178
<i>Goldberg: Excuse me.
With all of the skeletons</i>

02:58.179 --> 03:00.192
<i>in each and every one of our own closets,</i>

03:00.193 --> 03:02.422
<i>we probably should not
be talking about that.</i>

03:02.423 --> 03:05.473
<i>How about we just show the
people what this girl can do</i>

03:05.474 --> 03:07.069
<i>and let it speak for itself?</i>

03:07.070 --> 03:08.554
<i>Can you run the video, please?</i>

03:08.555 --> 03:11.353
<i>Hi, I'm Maddie, and this is
a song I wrote with my dad.</i>

03:12.250 --> 03:15.747
<i>♪ The shadows of regret ♪</i>

03:16.224 --> 03:19.394
<i>♪ the ghosts of things we said ♪</i>

03:20.048 --> 03:21.928
<i>♪ they've got me dead to right ♪</i>

03:21.929 --> 03:24.494
looks like the tabloids finally have
something other than you to talk about.

03:24.495 --> 03:26.932
She's a kid. I'd rather them talk about me.

03:28.192 --> 03:29.320
<i>♪ So he... ♪</i>

03:29.321 --> 03:31.125
So, how's the house for tomorrow?

03:31.126 --> 03:32.409
Better than Portland.

03:32.784 --> 03:34.882
Chicago is four times the size of Portland,

03:34.883 --> 03:36.951
so it'd just about have to be, wouldn't it?

03:36.952 --> 03:38.076
True.

03:38.077 --> 03:39.497
But "better than Portland"

03:39.498 --> 03:42.009
sounds more optimistic than "half full."

03:42.010 --> 03:43.974
And the country stations
still won't bring me in?

03:43.975 --> 03:44.918
Not even here?

03:44.919 --> 03:46.285
I have tried. Believe me.

03:46.286 --> 03:47.594
The only reason why I signed with Rayna

03:47.595 --> 03:49.535
is so that I could get back
into country's good graces,

03:49.536 --> 03:51.683
and that is not happening.

03:51.684 --> 03:53.437
Without country radio, I'm dead.

03:53.438 --> 03:55.565
They won't play me. They won't promote me.

03:55.566 --> 03:58.402
If only you knew somebody high
up in the radio business...

03:59.433 --> 04:01.334
Someone who might be willing to help,

04:01.335 --> 04:03.478
someone who just happens to be in Chicago

04:04.566 --> 04:06.209
right this very minute.

04:14.336 --> 04:15.490
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:15.899 --> 04:17.446
Oh, stay a little longer.

04:18.241 --> 04:19.447
I wish I could.

04:19.449 --> 04:21.310
Scarlett and me are
recording all day today.

04:21.312 --> 04:22.725
Got to take advantage of the time off,

04:22.726 --> 04:25.329
but I will definitely see you tonight.

04:32.540 --> 04:33.765
[Door opens]

04:35.122 --> 04:36.679
[Door closes]

04:39.581 --> 04:40.950
[Door opens]

04:40.951 --> 04:41.816
All righty.

04:41.817 --> 04:44.360
We got some coffee and some warm biscuits.

04:44.894 --> 04:46.422
Uh, they didn't have any raspberry jam,

04:46.423 --> 04:47.929
so I got blackberry.

04:47.930 --> 04:49.949
Hey. New head shots, right?

04:49.950 --> 04:52.644
What do you think about
this one? Too slutty?

04:52.645 --> 04:53.791
Well, you know, as a guy,

04:53.792 --> 04:56.209
there's no such thing as
"too slutty," so it's good.

04:56.210 --> 04:57.514
Shut up. [Chuckles]

04:57.515 --> 05:01.025
Oh, this was messengered
over while you were gone.

05:01.988 --> 05:06.656
Okay, I think I've narrowed
it down to three poses.

05:06.980 --> 05:10.700
What do you think...
fun, mysterious, or sexy?

05:13.744 --> 05:14.998
What is it?

05:17.292 --> 05:18.562
My royalties.

05:18.563 --> 05:20.684
$400,000?!

05:20.685 --> 05:22.324
Oh! Oh, my God!

05:22.325 --> 05:23.985
[Both laugh]

05:26.453 --> 05:28.963
[Knock on door] Hold on. Hold on.

05:29.751 --> 05:31.288
I know. I know.

05:31.289 --> 05:33.997
I'm sorry. I overslept.

05:33.998 --> 05:35.474
Surprise!

05:35.475 --> 05:37.298
Mama? [Chuckles]

05:37.299 --> 05:38.796
Wha... what are you doing here?

05:38.797 --> 05:40.188
You always say you have to work.

05:40.189 --> 05:42.466
Oh, don't even talk to me about work.

05:42.467 --> 05:44.989
The manager of that place was such a bitch.

05:44.990 --> 05:46.712
I do not know what her damage was.

05:46.713 --> 05:48.091
I think she was jealous of me or something

05:48.092 --> 05:50.411
because she started lying
about me to the owner

05:50.412 --> 05:53.437
and one thing led to another
and I just said good riddance.

05:53.438 --> 05:55.375
You know how those things
go? It happens, you know?

05:55.376 --> 05:56.206
Oh. Yeah, it happens. [Sighs]

05:56.207 --> 05:58.873
Oh! Wait till you see
what I brought you. Oh.

05:59.846 --> 06:03.073
Look at this beautiful,
beautiful thing from the airport.

06:03.074 --> 06:05.486
It's the Mississippi river to
remind you of home. [Chuckles]

06:05.487 --> 06:07.321
It's beautiful. Thank you.

06:07.322 --> 06:08.524
[Knock on door] Sweetie.

06:08.525 --> 06:09.891
- Hold on a second.
- Okay.

06:13.013 --> 06:14.339
Hey. You ready?

06:15.373 --> 06:16.710
Avery!

06:16.711 --> 06:18.216
Beverly. Hi.

06:18.217 --> 06:19.464
Hug me.

06:20.232 --> 06:23.287
Well, you didn't tell me the
two of you were back together.

06:23.288 --> 06:25.062
Oh, no, no. We're not together, mama.

06:25.063 --> 06:27.012
I'm producing Scarlett's album.

06:27.013 --> 06:28.434
We're recording it on the road.

06:28.435 --> 06:30.614
And we're actually running
late, so I got to go.

06:30.615 --> 06:32.146
Well, I'll get my purse.

06:32.870 --> 06:35.520
That is so exciting.

06:35.521 --> 06:37.883
Recording. Producing.

06:38.318 --> 06:40.094
[Reporters shouting indistinctly]

06:40.409 --> 06:41.518
Rayna!

06:42.102 --> 06:43.427
Is Deacon Daphne's father as well?

06:44.267 --> 06:45.722
[Shouting continues]

06:46.077 --> 06:47.196
Hey! Hey, sweetheart.

06:47.197 --> 06:48.138
Maddie! Maddie! Hey!

06:49.755 --> 06:51.700
Take your hands off her!

06:51.701 --> 06:54.405
You want a quote? Stay
the hell away from my kids!

06:56.103 --> 07:05.957
Synced and corrected by Nantinha
~ www.addic7ed.com ~

07:09.260 --> 07:11.189
Honey, I told you to take it down.

07:11.190 --> 07:12.970
[Voice breaking] I swear. I took it down!

07:12.971 --> 07:15.014
Well, then, how did it end
up on national television?

07:15.015 --> 07:17.262
Someone must have re-posted
it. What about Colt?

07:17.263 --> 07:18.391
He had the link on his iPad.

07:18.392 --> 07:20.325
No, I told him that he couldn't
post anything about you and Daphne.

07:20.326 --> 07:21.664
Oh, and I suppose your teenager

07:21.665 --> 07:24.440
- just does whatever you tell him to do.
- Teddy, he knew the girls were off-limits.

07:24.441 --> 07:25.786
- I hate this!
- Rayna: I know, honey.

07:25.787 --> 07:28.320
Listen, can we focus, please,
on what's happening here?

07:28.321 --> 07:29.386
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:29.387 --> 07:30.738
- I got here as soon as I could.
- Thank you.

07:30.739 --> 07:32.105
- Rayna: You know what, honey?
- Sweetheart.

07:32.106 --> 07:33.873
Could you go upstairs with
aunt Tandy for a little while?

07:33.874 --> 07:36.127
- Mom, I really want to listen.
- I need you to go upstairs, please.

07:36.128 --> 07:37.880
We need to handle this. Thank you. [Sighs]

07:37.881 --> 07:40.243
Hey, yeah, come with me. We'll
go upstairs, we'll read a book,

07:40.244 --> 07:42.101
and we will see you in a little while.

07:42.102 --> 07:43.639
Rayna: Doesn't matter how
that video got out there.

07:43.640 --> 07:46.494
Point is, it's out there, and
we're gonna have to fix it, okay?

07:46.495 --> 07:48.583
Okay. I'm gonna call for a
press conference, all right?

07:48.584 --> 07:49.664
I don't want to call a press conference.

07:49.665 --> 07:50.984
I don't want a bunch of people badgering us

07:50.985 --> 07:52.338
about stuff that's none
of their damn business.

07:52.339 --> 07:53.976
Okay, fine. Fine. Then what do you suggest?

07:53.977 --> 07:56.724
I suggest that we put out a press release.

07:56.725 --> 07:59.288
We tell them this is a personal
matter about our children,

07:59.289 --> 08:01.420
- and we ask them to respect our privacy.
- Well, good luck with that,

08:01.421 --> 08:03.735
<i>because those people
don't respect our privacy.</i>

08:03.736 --> 08:05.654
You saw what happened
at the school. [Sniffles]

08:05.655 --> 08:08.294
A-a statement is not gonna be
enough, not in this day and age.

08:08.295 --> 08:10.906
No way. Not... not with the
Internet and this 24-hour news cycle.

08:10.907 --> 08:12.676
It's not gonna go away by itself, Rayna.

08:21.154 --> 08:22.484
Okay.

08:24.759 --> 08:26.589
We just tell them the story.

08:29.104 --> 08:31.625
We're gonna have to be a united front.

08:31.626 --> 08:33.051
Have you talked to Deacon?

08:33.052 --> 08:34.642
'Cause he hasn't returned my phone calls.

08:34.643 --> 08:35.913
No.

08:35.914 --> 08:37.801
I mean, not since the concert last night.

08:37.802 --> 08:39.172
Well, I'm gonna have to go find him.

08:39.173 --> 08:40.571
- I'm going with you.
- No, you're not.

08:40.572 --> 08:41.890
No, Rayna, I can't help
but think this is my fault.

08:41.892 --> 08:43.501
She's right. He had the video.

08:43.503 --> 08:45.527
If it wasn't him, it
was one of his friends.

08:45.528 --> 08:48.282
This is what you get
paid for two hit songs?

08:48.283 --> 08:50.335
I thought the check for 10 grand was huge.

08:50.336 --> 08:51.283
[Chuckles]

08:51.284 --> 08:52.354
I should have bought a bigger TV.

08:52.655 --> 08:54.267
[Chuckles]

08:54.268 --> 08:56.116
- What are you doing?
- Buying plane tickets.

08:56.117 --> 08:57.732
[Chuckles] Tonight, I'm
taking you to dinner...

08:58.034 --> 08:59.666
In Paris. [Chuckles]

08:59.667 --> 09:02.151
- You're crazy. No.
- But... n-no, you're right.

09:02.152 --> 09:05.137
We should just go to the airport, see
where the next flight takes us, right?

09:05.138 --> 09:06.068
Gunnar.

09:06.069 --> 09:07.341
- What?
- Be serious.

09:07.342 --> 09:09.206
<i>I am serious. I am 100% serious.</i>

09:09.207 --> 09:10.297
We need to celebrate.

09:10.298 --> 09:13.291
<i>We do need to celebrate,
but we can do that here.</i>

09:13.292 --> 09:14.581
I have a meeting tomorrow.

09:14.582 --> 09:16.045
Yeah, all right. Yeah.

09:16.046 --> 09:17.902
Hey, can we buy a
motorcycle? Just... [Chuckles]

09:17.903 --> 09:20.734
You know what? I'm gonna hold
onto this for the next 48 hours,

09:21.048 --> 09:22.704
give you a chance to calm down.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.277
What? So you're gonna sit there

09:24.278 --> 09:26.651
and pretend like you're not
holding a check for 400 grand?

09:26.652 --> 09:27.961
It's not my money.

09:27.962 --> 09:30.013
Besides, my meeting
tomorrow's with the agency.

09:30.014 --> 09:33.298
[Chuckling] They already think I'm
a wide-eyed hick from the sticks.

09:33.299 --> 09:34.361
[Scoffs] You should've seen their faces

09:34.362 --> 09:36.345
when I handed them that
cd of me singin' in church

09:36.346 --> 09:39.791
like it was a real demo...
I looked like an idiot.

09:41.930 --> 09:44.552
Okay, wait. I know how I want to celebrate.

09:44.553 --> 09:46.084
It's... it's right here in Nashville.

09:46.085 --> 09:47.840
It is not dangerous.

09:48.422 --> 09:50.040
And most of all, it's
not even a splurge, okay?

09:50.041 --> 09:52.625
It's a necessity. Come on. Trust me.

09:52.626 --> 09:53.699
Grab your things.

09:53.700 --> 09:54.887
Where we going?

09:55.549 --> 09:56.579
Trust me.

09:57.424 --> 09:58.722
Reporter: We go live...

09:59.229 --> 10:00.425
Good lord.

10:00.426 --> 10:01.858
Luke: Must be a slow news day.

10:01.859 --> 10:03.004
Man, these people.

10:03.005 --> 10:04.540
I don't see Deacon's truck.

10:05.414 --> 10:06.913
- Where is he?
- You worried?

10:07.638 --> 10:09.880
You know what happened when
he found out about Maddie.

10:09.881 --> 10:11.645
Uh, you know, and he's
bounced back from that,

10:11.646 --> 10:13.049
and he's got a relationship now.

10:13.050 --> 10:14.977
But I don't know how
he's gonna react to this.

10:14.978 --> 10:16.365
He's a volatile guy.

10:16.366 --> 10:18.874
- You think he's drinkin' again?
- I hope not.

10:18.875 --> 10:21.276
For Maddie's sake. You
know, she loves him so much.

10:21.277 --> 10:24.956
Okay, suppose, I mean, worst
case, he is on a bender.

10:24.957 --> 10:26.077
Where should we look?

10:26.078 --> 10:27.259
I know where to look.

10:27.260 --> 10:29.425
I just... I feel like I
should probably go by myself.

10:29.426 --> 10:30.525
[Chuckling] Yeah, like hell.

10:30.526 --> 10:32.632
I know what Deacon's like when he's drunk.

10:32.633 --> 10:34.019
If you're going, I'm coming with you.

10:37.642 --> 10:40.802
I know it doesn't look like
much, but gets the job done.

10:41.143 --> 10:42.679
Wow.

10:42.680 --> 10:45.571
Recording sure has changed since my day.

10:45.572 --> 10:47.820
Looks like you could practically
cut an album on your phone.

10:48.654 --> 10:49.989
Play me something.

10:50.481 --> 10:51.501
Avery: Uh...

10:52.070 --> 10:54.225
I-I'm not really comfortable with that.

10:54.226 --> 10:57.509
I mean, uh, the mixes aren't
done, tracks are missing.

10:57.510 --> 10:58.711
He's a perfectionist.

10:58.712 --> 11:00.857
Hey. Sorry. I was just looking for Avery.

11:00.858 --> 11:02.465
Juliette Barnes.

11:02.466 --> 11:04.534
This is my mother... Beverly O'Connor.

11:04.535 --> 11:07.144
Oh, your mama. Nice to meet you.

11:07.145 --> 11:08.622
Well, nice to meet you, too.

11:08.623 --> 11:10.518
I feel like we're practically
family at this point.

11:10.519 --> 11:11.760
You've had my brother on your tour

11:11.761 --> 11:13.771
and got my daughter on your tour,

11:13.772 --> 11:16.013
and next time, you're
just gonna have to take me.

11:16.014 --> 11:17.300
Are you in the business?

11:17.301 --> 11:20.771
Well, Deacon and I used to write
together and sing around town.

11:20.772 --> 11:22.618
And I was actually the one that
said, "let's go to Nashville,"

11:22.619 --> 11:26.216
but then I had Scarlett,
so there went that idea.

11:26.217 --> 11:27.678
[Chuckles]

11:27.679 --> 11:29.005
You were lookin' for me?

11:29.307 --> 11:31.466
Yes. Can I talk to you for a second?

11:31.467 --> 11:32.485
Sure.

11:32.486 --> 11:33.803
Be right back.

11:39.034 --> 11:40.414
Well, well.

11:40.415 --> 11:43.144
On tour with Luke Wheeler
and Juliette Barnes,

11:43.145 --> 11:46.213
workin' with Zac Brown, recording a record.

11:48.770 --> 11:50.506
Unbelievable.

11:52.922 --> 11:55.058
- I want to run something by you.
- Okay.

11:55.059 --> 11:56.876
Okay, Glenn and I were talking about

11:56.877 --> 11:58.298
the whole country radio issue,

11:58.299 --> 12:01.885
and Glenn came up with an idea.

12:01.886 --> 12:03.560
I don't think you're gonna like it, though.

12:03.561 --> 12:04.886
Why is that?

12:04.887 --> 12:07.335
He wants me to ask
Charlie Wentworth for help.

12:07.336 --> 12:08.667
He's in town,

12:08.668 --> 12:12.284
and, you know, we left
off on good terms, I think,

12:12.285 --> 12:15.392
and he does own half of the
radio stations in the country.

12:15.393 --> 12:17.544
But I know it's Charlie,
at the end of the day,

12:17.545 --> 12:19.738
and that might be really
uncomfortable for you.

12:19.739 --> 12:21.219
I think it's a smart idea.

12:22.177 --> 12:23.634
- You do?
- Yeah.

12:23.635 --> 12:26.170
If he can get you back on the
radio, you got to make the call.

12:26.171 --> 12:27.450
Are you... Sure?

12:27.451 --> 12:29.534
I-I don't want you to be
uncomfortable or anything.

12:29.535 --> 12:30.806
That's got to be...

12:33.281 --> 12:34.524
Make the call.

12:34.848 --> 12:35.921
Okay.

12:39.678 --> 12:41.909
This explains why he
wasn't answering his phone.

12:41.910 --> 12:43.629
There's no cell service out here.

12:58.173 --> 12:59.374
Deacon?

13:04.705 --> 13:06.175
Hey, Deacon?

13:11.090 --> 13:13.396
- What the hell, Rayna?
- What the hell?

13:14.768 --> 13:16.340
- Damn it.
- Luke: Whoa. Whoa.

13:16.341 --> 13:17.844
Take it easy, now. [Scoffs]

13:17.845 --> 13:21.428
- Why'd you do this? Why did you...
- I didn't drink, Rayna. All right?

13:21.429 --> 13:23.379
I poured it out the second
I got here, threw it in...

13:23.380 --> 13:25.365
- and just trashed the place, too, really?
- I'm redecorating.

13:25.995 --> 13:27.433
[Chuckles] I've seen you redecorate.

13:27.434 --> 13:28.480
Yeah, well, you're seeing it again.

13:28.481 --> 13:30.671
Maybe you can take your
bodyguard here and just go.

13:30.672 --> 13:32.614
Luke, can you give us a second, please?

13:35.104 --> 13:36.350
Yeah.

13:36.763 --> 13:39.113
- I'll be outside.
- Thanks.

13:43.898 --> 13:45.273
How the hell could you bring him up here?

13:45.274 --> 13:47.165
'Cause I didn't know what I
was gonna find when I got here.

13:47.166 --> 13:48.143
What are you even doing here?

13:48.144 --> 13:50.134
I have been trying to call
you for the last 24 hours.

13:50.135 --> 13:53.669
You can't just run away like
this every time things get hard!

13:53.670 --> 13:55.782
It's not even your
business, Rayna, all right?

13:55.783 --> 13:57.412
- What are you talkin' about?
- It's none of your business at all!

13:57.413 --> 13:59.052
- Did she call you?
- Who?

13:59.053 --> 13:59.997
Megan!

14:00.714 --> 14:01.787
No.

14:03.181 --> 14:04.655
Why the hell are you here?

14:04.656 --> 14:07.382
Because the entire world
knows about our daughter.

14:16.893 --> 14:18.553
Maddie Claybourne, huh?

14:18.554 --> 14:20.138
Yeah, she was mad at Teddy,

14:20.899 --> 14:22.354
didn't think it through.

14:25.602 --> 14:26.874
[Sighs]

14:28.538 --> 14:29.921
What do you want me to do?

14:29.922 --> 14:31.689
I think we're gonna have
to confront it head on.

14:32.250 --> 14:34.305
And that means all three of us.

14:34.306 --> 14:35.721
Now, you, me, and Teddy?

14:35.722 --> 14:37.273
- Yeah.
- One big, happy family?

14:37.274 --> 14:38.921
- Yeah.
- No.

14:38.922 --> 14:40.215
You're not listening to me.

14:40.216 --> 14:43.103
Your front lawn right now
is teeming with reporters.

14:43.104 --> 14:44.735
