to think about her right now.

15:03.117 --> 15:04.556
I do think about her. Okay, Rayna?

15:04.557 --> 15:06.764
I think about her all the
time, every single day,

15:06.765 --> 15:08.731
and there is nothing
I would not do for her,

15:08.732 --> 15:10.451
but I can't be with him in a room

15:10.452 --> 15:11.860
'cause if I am, I'm gonna kill him

15:12.244 --> 15:13.739
right in front of her
and in front of everybody!

15:13.740 --> 15:15.452
That's not gonna help no one!

15:16.988 --> 15:18.324
Why?

15:19.924 --> 15:21.525
You ask him.

15:23.764 --> 15:26.011
I hate the way she acts
like everything's fine.

15:26.012 --> 15:28.155
Like, in front of people,
we're best friends.

15:28.156 --> 15:29.499
What do you want her to do?

15:29.500 --> 15:32.075
Acknowledge something. Apologize.

15:32.076 --> 15:33.811
I know this is so stupid. I'm grown.

15:33.812 --> 15:37.004
I should just get over it,
but it... I can't help it.

15:37.005 --> 15:39.307
Every second I spend
with her feels like a lie,

15:39.308 --> 15:41.531
and I don't like pretending that it's not.

15:41.532 --> 15:43.204
Then why do you do it?

15:44.461 --> 15:47.587
Look, Scarlett, I've heard you
call your mom dozens of times,

15:47.588 --> 15:49.820
give her updates, say, "I love you."

15:50.148 --> 15:51.228
Yeah.

15:51.229 --> 15:54.084
Never really talk about
anything of substance with her.

15:54.085 --> 15:55.588
It's just a habit.

15:56.389 --> 15:58.244
And of course I love her. She's my mama.

15:58.772 --> 16:01.011
Doesn't give her the right
to treat you like she does.

16:01.012 --> 16:03.436
No, but we both know how she grew up.

16:03.932 --> 16:05.452
She can't help the way she is.

16:06.877 --> 16:08.404
Gunnar, this is crazy.

16:08.405 --> 16:10.683
<i>No, it is not. It is perfectly rational.</i>

16:10.684 --> 16:12.075
