Hey! Is that really what you think of me?

26:58.943 --> 27:00.279
I'm some kind of monster?

27:00.280 --> 27:02.080
You're not a monster. You're my mother.

27:02.424 --> 27:05.838
And I love you, but you know exactly
what you've done to me my whole life.

27:05.839 --> 27:06.767
[Scoffs]

27:07.335 --> 27:09.390
<i>What I've done to you?</i>

27:09.391 --> 27:10.134
- Hey!
- Hey!

27:10.135 --> 27:13.454
What I did was provide
for you my whole life!

27:13.455 --> 27:16.174
I put a roof over your
head and food on the table.

27:16.175 --> 27:18.517
All of this is because of me.

27:18.518 --> 27:20.837
<i>- Your talent is my talent!
- No, mommy! No!</i>

27:20.838 --> 27:24.188
I gave up my dreams for you.

27:24.189 --> 27:25.596
<i>No! Leave me alone! Let me go! Mom!</i>

27:25.597 --> 27:27.356
And now you're living the
life I should have had!

27:27.357 --> 27:29.269
It should be me up on that stage!

27:29.270 --> 27:32.256
You think your childhood
was such a tragedy? [Gasps]

27:32.257 --> 27:35.160
Your life was a picnic compared to mine.

27:35.161 --> 27:37.424
[Gasping] [Voice breaking] You
have no idea what it was like

27:37.425 --> 27:39.304
growing up in that...

27:39.305 --> 27:42.105
Oh, you never had any idea. [Sobbing]

27:49.642 --> 27:52.122
Hey. Want to play for a little while?

27:53.818 --> 27:55.546
Why?

27:55.547 --> 27:58.010
[Chuckles lightly] What do you mean why?

27:58.011 --> 27:59.058
You love to play.

27:59.059 --> 28:01.042
I don't want to sing with you anymore.

28:02.027 --> 28:03.714
But we always sing together.

28:05.227 --> 28:07.234
Then why'd you post that video?

28:07.898 --> 28:09.762
Why'd you change your last name?

28:09.763 --> 28:11.666
Don't you want to be my sister anymore?

28:11.667 --> 28:14.115
<i>Of course I do, Daphne. I am your sister.</i>

28:14.587 --> 28:15.874
Hey, look at me.

28:16.619 --> 28:17.993
That video was a mistake,

28:17.994 --> 28:19.905
and if I could take it back, I would.

28:19.906 --> 28:24.354
I was just mad and frustrated,

28:24.355 --> 28:27.714
and I did something really, really stupid.

28:27.715 --> 28:29.123
I screwed up.

28:29.819 --> 28:31.074
Please forgive me.

28:33.323 --> 28:35.138
Better yet, sing with me?

28:36.242 --> 28:38.426
♪ I've been tryin' to do it right ♪

28:38.866 --> 28:42.298
♪ I've been livin' a lonely life ♪

28:42.299 --> 28:44.899
♪ I've been sleepin' here instead ♪

28:45.355 --> 28:48.554
♪ I've been sleepin' in my bed ♪

28:48.914 --> 28:53.098
♪ Sleepin' in my bed ♪

28:55.107 --> 28:58.499
♪ Still sitting on Daphne's bed ♪

29:09.506 --> 29:12.423
♪ So show me family ♪

29:12.795 --> 29:15.986
♪ All the blood that I would bleed ♪

29:15.987 --> 29:18.538
♪ I don't know where I belong ♪

29:19.239 --> 29:22.346
♪ I don't know where I went wrong ♪

29:23.275 --> 29:26.219
♪ I can write a song ♪

43:55.078 --> 29:30.290
♪ I belong with you,
you belong with me ♪

29:30.291 --> 29:33.666
♪ You're my sweetheart ♪

29:34.202 --> 29:37.401
♪ I belong with you,
you belong with me ♪

29:37.402 --> 29:41.266
♪ You're my sweetheart ♪

29:43.499 --> 29:45.386
I'm so sorry about all this.

29:45.387 --> 29:48.418
Colt's still trying to
find out who posted it,

29:48.419 --> 29:50.482
and it sounds like it
was a friend of a friend.

29:51.451 --> 29:54.874
You know... It really doesn't matter

29:55.178 --> 29:57.105
whose fault it is at this point.

29:57.106 --> 29:59.219
I just want to get this thing done,

29:59.699 --> 30:01.810
get our kids' lives back to normal.

30:01.811 --> 30:03.682
Luke, do you think you could go out

30:03.683 --> 30:05.097
and see if Teddy's here yet?

30:05.098 --> 30:06.569
He should have been here a while ago.

30:06.570 --> 30:08.329
- Absolutely. Yeah.
- Thank you.

30:08.330 --> 30:09.458
Yeah.

30:11.242 --> 30:12.186
[Door opens]

30:12.498 --> 30:13.851
[Door closes]

30:16.242 --> 30:17.658
It's gonna be okay.

30:18.626 --> 30:19.769
It is.

30:19.770 --> 30:23.545
Robin is fair, and she's responsible.

30:23.546 --> 30:25.938
What if I had told Deacon the truth?

30:26.659 --> 30:27.793
What if I had done that

30:27.794 --> 30:30.113
and he just stopped drinking that very day?

30:30.114 --> 30:32.161
I was there. I saw what he was like.

30:32.162 --> 30:34.073
Maybe becoming a father
would have been the thing

30:34.074 --> 30:35.921
that finally got rid of his demons.

30:35.922 --> 30:37.874
I don't think that's how addiction works.

30:37.875 --> 30:40.267
You wanted to make a
better life for Maddie.

30:40.268 --> 30:42.011
Yeah, but what's a better life, really?

30:42.012 --> 30:45.027
I mean, I'm divorced from Teddy.

30:45.028 --> 30:47.803
He's become somebody
I don't even recognize.

30:47.804 --> 30:49.756
Maddie's life has blown up.

30:49.757 --> 30:51.563
Our family's crazy. [Chuckles lightly]

30:51.564 --> 30:53.420
What's so special about this life?

30:53.724 --> 30:55.019
Really? Los Angeles?

30:55.020 --> 30:56.651
Zoey: Relax. I'm not moving there.

30:56.652 --> 30:59.011
I'm just... Thinking about
taking a couple weeks off

30:59.012 --> 31:00.707
to explore the possibilities,

31:00.708 --> 31:03.091
maybe meet with a couple
of Jackie's connections,

31:03.092 --> 31:04.948
and pick up an audition or two.

31:04.949 --> 31:07.100
You haven't even given
Nashville a shot yet.

31:07.484 --> 31:09.963
I mean, you only just got
your audition stuff together.

31:09.964 --> 31:12.315
Why don't you chill, see
what happens here first?

31:12.316 --> 31:13.283
I don't know.

31:13.284 --> 31:15.611
Jackie seems to think I
should be more proactive.

31:15.612 --> 31:17.675
Be more proactive here. Quit your job.

31:17.676 --> 31:18.939
Let music be your main focus.

31:18.940 --> 31:21.172
Are you crazy? How am I gonna pay my rent?

31:21.173 --> 31:24.379
You can move in here.
I'll take care of you.

31:24.380 --> 31:26.051
- Gunnar.
- You saw the check.

31:26.052 --> 31:27.587
There's more where that came from.

31:27.588 --> 31:29.532
And that is enough for both of us, okay?

31:30.420 --> 31:33.914
That is an incredibly generous offer,

31:34.218 --> 31:35.737
but listen to yourself.

31:35.738 --> 31:37.986
I don't... Need a sugar daddy.

31:39.682 --> 31:42.042
You know, it doesn't sound so
nice when you say it like that.

31:42.618 --> 31:43.746
I'm sorry.

31:44.731 --> 31:47.297
I really am grateful that
you would do that for me.

31:47.298 --> 31:51.178
I just... I left home to
stand on my own two feet,

31:51.610 --> 31:53.242
see what I'm capable of.

31:53.970 --> 31:57.409
Moving in would feel like
a step backward, you know?

31:57.410 --> 31:59.969
I just want to help you
make your dreams come true.

31:59.970 --> 32:01.738
But what about your dreams?

32:02.226 --> 32:03.993
<i>What about what you want?</i>

32:03.994 --> 32:06.218
That's what you should
be spending your money on.

32:09.658 --> 32:12.274
- What are you doing here?
- I'm a guest of Juliette's.

32:12.275 --> 32:13.750
She said you were sending programmers.

32:13.751 --> 32:15.494
Didn't mention anything
about you coming by.

32:15.495 --> 32:16.919
Yeah, I suddenly got nostalgic

32:16.920 --> 32:19.582
about being backstage at
a Juliette Barnes concert.

32:20.351 --> 32:22.261
It's intoxicating, really.

32:22.262 --> 32:23.558
Just couldn't keep away.

32:24.391 --> 32:26.622
Hey, just to be clear.

32:27.600 --> 32:29.318
I don't like the way you treated her.

32:29.319 --> 32:31.086
- Oh.
- She deserved better.

32:31.087 --> 32:32.631
- Mm-hmm.
- She still does.

32:32.967 --> 32:34.383
And I suppose that's you, is it?

32:34.384 --> 32:35.990
She certainly seems to think so.

32:36.751 --> 32:38.961
Look, mate, um [Clears throat]

32:38.962 --> 32:40.466
You're out of your league.

32:41.066 --> 32:42.938
Sooner or later, she's gonna realize that.

32:43.282 --> 32:46.106
It's always about money and
power with you, isn't it?

32:46.812 --> 32:48.498
Would've thought you'd learn by now.

32:48.818 --> 32:50.411
You can't buy Juliette.

32:50.842 --> 32:52.346
- Hm.
- You never could.

32:52.674 --> 32:53.930
It's over, Charlie.

32:55.379 --> 32:56.770
Move on.

32:59.576 --> 33:00.791
[Knock on door]

33:00.792 --> 33:02.040
Juliette: Come in.

33:02.816 --> 33:04.424
- Hey.
- Hey.

33:05.168 --> 33:06.352
Um...

33:07.856 --> 33:09.335
Can I talk to you a minute?

33:09.336 --> 33:10.568
Yeah.

33:11.361 --> 33:13.008
I feel really stupid asking,

33:13.009 --> 33:14.422
and I know I shouldn't,

33:15.393 --> 33:17.512
but I-I was wondering if I...

33:18.195 --> 33:19.968
If could have tonight off.

33:20.393 --> 33:22.776
Uh, this isn't Dairy Queen,

33:22.777 --> 33:26.111
where you can just switch
shifts with somebody, Scarlett.

33:26.112 --> 33:28.872
You're... It. You're my opening act.

33:28.873 --> 33:30.768
I kn... I know, and I shouldn't be asking.

33:30.769 --> 33:35.153
I know. I-I can't believe
I am, but I... I'm asking.

33:35.601 --> 33:37.808
Please don't make me go out there tonight.

33:37.809 --> 33:39.424
Is this about your mama?

33:40.031 --> 33:41.711
Girl, if there is anybody

33:41.712 --> 33:44.256
who understands what you're
going through, it's me.

33:44.257 --> 33:45.816
But you got to figure out a way

33:45.817 --> 33:48.312
to get up there on that stage and smile,

33:48.313 --> 33:50.703
- even when you feel like crying.
- I know.

33:51.326 --> 33:52.743
Okay?

33:52.744 --> 33:55.239
Good. There's a lot of
important radio people out there,

33:55.240 --> 33:57.504
so I need you to give them a good show.

33:57.505 --> 33:58.832
I will.

34:04.304 --> 34:05.648
[Door slams]

34:06.424 --> 34:07.912
[Sobbing]

34:09.623 --> 34:10.920
[Sniffling]

34:27.312 --> 34:28.235
Robin, you ready?

34:28.235 --> 34:29.554
<i>- Robin: All set here.
- Okay.</i>

34:29.556 --> 34:31.266
- Rayna, Teddy, you guys ready?
- Yeah.

34:31.268 --> 34:32.808
Rayna: Yeah. I'll give
you a 10-second lead-in.

34:33.657 --> 34:36.013
Excuse me. Y'all got another chair?

34:37.254 --> 34:38.204
Um...

34:38.205 --> 34:41.045
Uh... Can you give us
one quick second, please?

34:41.045 --> 34:43.126
- Man: Sure. Get a chair.
- Hey.

34:45.014 --> 34:46.348
I didn't think you were coming.

34:46.349 --> 34:48.108
I'm here. What do you want me to say?

34:48.636 --> 34:50.971
Well, I want you to tell the truth.

34:50.972 --> 34:52.985
- You sure about that?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

34:52.987 --> 34:53.914
That's what I'll do.

34:53.915 --> 34:55.512
Sorry, folks. New York
is on a tight schedule.

34:55.513 --> 34:57.288
- Can we go?
- Let's do it.

34:57.289 --> 34:58.665
Okay, let's do it.

35:03.570 --> 35:08.848
And 10, 9, 8, 7, 6...

35:08.849 --> 35:11.825
5, 4, 3...

35:19.740 --> 35:21.947
<i>Robin: Rayna, Deacon, mayor Conrad,</i>

35:21.948 --> 35:23.892
<i>thanks so much for
agreeing to speak with us.</i>

35:23.893 --> 35:25.460
- Thank you, Robin.
- Rayna: Thank you for having us.

35:25.461 --> 35:27.567
<i>Now, Rayna, it's widely known</i>

35:27.568 --> 35:30.408
<i>that you and Deacon did
date back in the day.</i>

35:30.409 --> 35:31.296
<i>Is that correct?</i>

35:31.297 --> 35:33.400
Yes, we did, and... and, um...

35:33.401 --> 35:37.456
Deacon has always been a very
important part of... of my life

35:37.457 --> 35:40.056
and our lives, both
personally and professionally.

35:40.057 --> 35:42.503
And, uh, today, we're
really here to clarify...

35:42.504 --> 35:43.215
I'm sorry, Robin.

35:43.216 --> 35:45.760
Why don't we just...
Get right down to this?

35:45.761 --> 35:48.017
Uh, yes, I am the biological father

35:48.433 --> 35:50.072
of Rayna's oldest daughter.

35:50.073 --> 35:52.241
So, why was she raised by another man?

35:54.313 --> 35:56.207
It's because I'm an alcoholic.

35:56.208 --> 35:58.599
Uh, that's actually probably
too nice a word for it.

35:58.600 --> 36:00.456
Back then, I was just a plain, old drunk.

36:00.457 --> 36:02.800
Rayna tried more times
than I care to admit...

36:02.801 --> 36:04.840
she tried to get me into
rehab, get me fixed up,

36:04.841 --> 36:07.617
but, uh... I just wasn't
ready to be a father.

36:07.929 --> 36:11.328
<i>So, Rayna, when you found
out you were pregnant...</i>

36:11.329 --> 36:13.159
Deacon and I were no longer together,

36:13.160 --> 36:14.711
and I was dating Teddy

36:14.712 --> 36:16.840
and I told Teddy about the baby right away.

36:16.841 --> 36:18.488
We were always very honest about that.

36:18.489 --> 36:19.472
Teddy: That's true, Robin.

36:19.473 --> 36:21.336
I-I did know about the baby
right from the beginning,

36:21.337 --> 36:24.424
and while I may not be
Maddie's biological father,

36:24.425 --> 36:27.367
I can promise you that
I... I fell in love with her

36:27.368 --> 36:30.343
from the moment I held her
in my arms for the first time.

36:30.344 --> 36:31.736
<i>And what about you, Deacon?</i>

36:32.193 --> 36:33.865
<i>Do you have a relationship with Maddie?</i>

36:34.265 --> 36:36.201
Yes, uh, I do.

36:37.161 --> 36:39.208
It's the single best part of my life.

36:39.209 --> 36:41.856
She is an exceptional young lady,

36:41.857 --> 36:45.495
and Rayna, here, along with mayor Conrad...

36:45.496 --> 36:47.487
well, they done an
amazing job raising her up.

36:47.488 --> 36:49.616
<i>Well, you clearly aren't the only one</i>

36:49.617 --> 36:51.336
<i>who thinks Maddie is exceptional.</i>

36:51.337 --> 36:54.776
<i>Her video now has over 900,000 hits.</i>

36:54.777 --> 36:57.160
<i>People are saying she's
the next Taylor Swift!</i>

36:57.161 --> 36:58.080
Oh. [Chuckles]

36:58.081 --> 37:00.704
<i>So can we expect a debut
album any time soon?</i>

37:00.705 --> 37:02.913
- Uh... No, ma'am.
- [Chuckling] Oh, no.

37:22.852 --> 37:25.195
<i>Again, thanks so much for being here.</i>

37:25.196 --> 37:27.003
- Thanks, Robin.
- Man: And we're out.

37:27.004 --> 37:28.787
Robin, thank you. We appreciate it.

37:28.788 --> 37:30.828
<i>Robin: Oh, any time,
Rayna. You take care, now.</i>

37:31.676 --> 37:32.860
You too.

37:36.243 --> 37:37.515
Tandy: I think that went perfectly.

37:37.516 --> 37:38.691
- You do?
- Yeah.

37:38.692 --> 37:40.835
Yep. Yeah. It totally diffused the story.

37:40.836 --> 37:43.120
Good. I hope you're right.

37:44.624 --> 37:45.583
You know what?

37:45.584 --> 37:48.510
I'm gonna go on home and let
y'all have some family time.

37:48.511 --> 37:49.936
- All right. Thanks, babe.
- Yep.

37:50.440 --> 37:51.784
Call me later.

37:53.640 --> 37:55.264
[Reporters shouting indistinctly]

37:55.624 --> 37:57.296
Are you gonna be dad number three?

37:58.176 --> 38:00.000
[Shouting continues]

38:05.505 --> 38:06.944
Damn it!

38:09.160 --> 38:11.368
- Take me to the airport.
- Yes, sir.

38:13.176 --> 38:14.463
Hey.

38:14.464 --> 38:16.008
Where were you all day, huh?

38:16.352 --> 38:19.307
[Slurred] I smell the flowers
in my room all the way out here.

38:19.308 --> 38:20.868
[Chuckles lightly] You been drinking?

38:21.244 --> 38:22.755
No. Go away.

38:22.756 --> 38:24.547
- Wait, Scarlett, hold on.
- Get off me!

38:25.316 --> 38:26.620
You stay away from me.

38:27.820 --> 38:29.515
Hey, go get Juliette right away.

38:29.516 --> 38:30.820
Tell her it's an emergency.

38:33.046 --> 38:34.334
- Hey.
- Hey.

38:34.862 --> 38:36.238
I wanted to say thank you

38:36.662 --> 38:38.054
for doing that.

38:38.574 --> 38:40.838
- You ran out of there so fast.
- Yeah.

38:41.566 --> 38:42.726
You were right.

38:44.198 --> 38:45.638
We needed to do it.

38:46.534 --> 38:47.670
How's she doing?

38:48.510 --> 38:49.774
I don't know.

38:50.910 --> 38:52.046
[Sighs]

38:53.366 --> 38:54.814
You should've told me, Ray.

38:56.698 --> 38:58.500
I'm sorry. Look, I was...

38:58.884 --> 39:01.091
A mess when you found
out you were pregnant.

39:01.092 --> 39:02.451
I get that.

39:02.452 --> 39:05.244
But I got better, and...

39:07.412 --> 39:10.371
I've been good a long time, right?

39:13.364 --> 39:18.035
So why didn't you tell me when
she was like... 3, you know?

39:18.036 --> 39:19.708
Or 5 or 10 or...

39:22.140 --> 39:23.371
Why didn't you just give me

39:23.875 --> 39:25.643
a little more time to be her daddy?

39:27.453 --> 39:29.463
You were always a part
of her life, you know?

39:29.464 --> 39:30.959
- I mean, I made sure of that.
- Oh, no, Ray... no.

39:30.960 --> 39:32.336
You got to watch her grow up.

39:33.600 --> 39:35.046
It's not the same.

39:35.047 --> 39:36.723
You know that's not the same, Rayna.

39:37.307 --> 39:38.579
You ever sing her to sleep?

39:38.915 --> 39:40.179
Mm-hmm.

39:40.180 --> 39:41.443
I never did.

39:41.444 --> 39:44.235
And I never got to hold
her when she was scared,

39:44.236 --> 39:47.507
or, uh... I don't know...
feel her clinging to my leg

39:47.508 --> 39:49.587
when she was shy around a stranger.

39:49.588 --> 39:51.827
Yeah, I was there all the time, but...

39:54.067 --> 39:56.579
I didn't know, you know? God, help me.

39:56.580 --> 39:58.883
The hard part is, is that right
now, I still wouldn't know.

39:58.884 --> 40:00.803
If she hadn't found out,
Rayna, I still wouldn't know.

40:00.804 --> 40:02.011
You'd be sitting right in that chair

40:02.012 --> 40:04.587
lying to my face right now and
every other day the rest of my life.

40:04.588 --> 40:06.395
You don't know that. I mean... [Sighs]

40:07.988 --> 40:09.250
Look, I'm sorry.

40:09.251 --> 40:11.787
I went there, and I did what
I needed to do for my daughter,

40:11.788 --> 40:14.148
but that's all I got
for you right now, Rayna.

40:15.044 --> 40:18.499
<i>Our daughter. She's our daughter, Deacon.</i>

40:18.500 --> 40:20.995
And I've done what I
had to do for her, too.

40:20.996 --> 40:22.930
You think I wanted it like this?

40:22.931 --> 40:24.795
I wanted to be your wife.

40:25.331 --> 40:28.099
I wanted us to raise her up together

40:28.100 --> 40:30.044
in a wonderful, loving home

40:30.364 --> 40:32.772
that you could not provide.

40:36.052 --> 40:38.402
I cried myself to sleep
about that for a year,

40:38.403 --> 40:40.234
I wanted it so bad.

40:40.235 --> 40:41.378
And, you know, you're right,

40:41.379 --> 40:42.643
I could have told you

40:42.644 --> 40:44.883
at some point down the
line, I guess, but when?

40:44.884 --> 40:46.307
You know, when, really, is a good time

40:46.308 --> 40:49.235
to blow up your kid's life?

40:49.236 --> 40:50.603
And when you did find out,

40:50.604 --> 40:52.147
did you just scoop her up in your arms

40:52.148 --> 40:53.258
and tell her how much you loved her

40:53.259 --> 40:55.082
and you were so proud of her?

40:55.083 --> 40:56.491
No.

40:58.452 --> 41:00.427
You got drunk.

41:00.428 --> 41:02.324
You got drunk, and I almost died.

41:03.364 --> 41:05.035
I lied to you. I did.

41:05.036 --> 41:07.163
And I bet you resent the
hell out of me for that,

41:07.164 --> 41:09.210
but I guarantee you, I resent you even more

41:09.211 --> 41:11.795
for putting us in this
position in the first place.

41:15.124 --> 41:17.547
Oh, I love your boots.
Where'd you get those from?

41:17.548 --> 41:18.707
Around here?

41:18.708 --> 41:20.619
Hey, back off! Excuse me?

41:20.620 --> 41:21.936
Scarlett, you need to come
with me right now. Come on.

41:21.937 --> 41:22.920
No, I've got to go do the show.

41:22.921 --> 41:24.376
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Leave her alone, mate.

41:24.377 --> 41:25.648
<i>You leave her alone!</i>

41:25.649 --> 41:26.672
Scarlett's off-limits!

41:26.673 --> 41:28.349
Oh, really? You laying claim
to that one, too, are you?

41:28.350 --> 41:29.685
Is there anyone here you're not dating?

41:29.686 --> 41:31.053
What the hell's going on? [Crowd cheering]

41:31.054 --> 41:32.725
I don't know. Better ask your boyfriend.

41:32.726 --> 41:33.821
Emcee: Ladies and gentlemen,

41:33.822 --> 41:36.406
put your hands together
for miss Scarlett O'Connor!

41:36.407 --> 41:37.439
Scarlett!

41:38.097 --> 41:39.815
Y'all ready to have some fun?!

41:40.295 --> 41:41.462
What was that?

41:42.030 --> 41:43.734
I don't know. Something's wrong.

41:44.056 --> 41:45.461
I'm not talking about Scarlett.

41:45.462 --> 41:48.237
Wha... it's okay for Charlie to kiss me,

41:48.238 --> 41:49.797
but you won't let him anywhere
near your ex-girlfriend?

41:49.798 --> 41:52.191
<i>Wait. You said he tried to kiss you.</i>

41:52.895 --> 41:54.246
You look so beautiful!

41:54.247 --> 41:56.526
Thank you so much for coming to see me.

41:56.974 --> 41:58.805
<i>Beverly: [Echoing] It should
be me up on that stage!</i>

41:58.806 --> 41:59.693
<i>I should be up there!</i>

42:00.509 --> 42:02.405
[Music plays]

42:04.149 --> 42:06.212
<i>All of this is because of me.</i>

42:06.213 --> 42:08.532
<i>Your talent is my talent!</i>

42:08.533 --> 42:10.420
<i>Think you're such a tragedy?</i>

42:10.421 --> 42:13.469
<i>Your childhood was a
picnic compared to mine.</i>

42:13.797 --> 42:15.597
[Music stops]

42:19.533 --> 42:20.852
[Audience murmuring]

42:20.853 --> 42:22.156
Scarlett: I'm sorry.

42:22.157 --> 42:23.787
[Crying] Please don't do that.

42:23.788 --> 42:26.036
Why are you doing this to me?

42:26.037 --> 42:27.420
What did I do to you?

42:27.421 --> 42:28.941
You make me so angry.

42:29.429 --> 42:31.157
[Shouting indistinctly]

42:35.813 --> 42:38.349
Aah! No, no, no, no, no!

42:38.757 --> 42:41.524
Please stop. Please stop.

42:41.525 --> 42:43.629
- Please stop. No.
- Scarlett.

42:43.949 --> 42:46.198
Oh, my God.

